@danielezonca
Previously, TestingModelImplementationProvider was mapped to RegressionModel, so those tests returned a "KiePMMLTestingModel" (sort of a mock).
But with MiningModel tests (that needs all the real ModelImplementationProviders), having two ModelImplementationProviders mapped to the same model (Regression) may lead to error. So TestingModelImplementationProvider currently is mapped to a (fake) model, but then those methods returns an empty Optional. I have to find a proper fix for that

